edu.ucla.sspace.vector

Class AbstractVector<T extends Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ucla.sspace.vector.AbstractVector<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Vector<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDoubleVector, AbstractIntegerVector, SparseHashVector

    public abstract class AbstractVector<T extends Number>
extends Object
implements Vector<T>
    An abstract base class that provides default implementations of common methods in Vector. Vector implementations need only implement Vector.length() and Vector.getValue(int) functionality to be read-only vectors.
